Somei-yoshino pink cherry tree blossom only for a week. It looks fantastically beautiful in this period and is celebrated. These short-lived bossoms were used as symbols for young Japanese in war: expected to bloom and fall for the Emperor. The blossoms adorned kamikaze planes.

In April, pink cherry trees blossom briefly throughout Japan. While regarded as benign symbols of beauty, they are actually the product of the far right/ultra-nationalist Showa inter-war period in the 1920s and 1930s. Before then, there was a much wider variety of species.
